cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with graph theory and parameterized complexity, which are topics covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The focus on graph orientation and deletion suggests categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of treewidth and clique-width as parameters suggests categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper's connections to load balancing and optimization suggest cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible category.
